Automating Email Sending using PyAutoGUI (Python)
Today I built a simple automation using Python to open Gmail and send an email automatically using PyAutoGUI.
Automate the following steps:
1.	Open Gmail in browser
2.	Click Compose
3.	Enter recipient email
4.	Add subject & body
5.	Send the email
Tools Used:
1.	Python
2.	pyautogui
3.	pyperclip
4.	webbrowser module

import pyautogui
import time
import webbrowser
import pyperclip

# Enable failsafe (Move mouse to top-left corner to stop script)
pyautogui.FAILSAFE = True

# Step 1: Open Gmail
webbrowser.open("https://mail.google.com/")
time.sleep(12)  # Wait for Gmail to load

# Step 2: Focus browser window
pyautogui.click(pyautogui.size()[0]//2, pyautogui.size()[1]//2)
time.sleep(2)

# Step 3: Press 'C' to Compose (Keyboard shortcut must be enabled in Gmail)
pyautogui.press('c')
time.sleep(3)

# Step 4: Enter recipient
pyperclip.copy("karthiksraja7@gmail.com")
pyautogui.hotkey("ctrl", "v")
time.sleep(1)
pyautogui.press("tab")

# Step 5: Enter Subject
pyperclip.copy("Test Mail from PyAutoGUI")
pyautogui.hotkey("ctrl", "v")
time.sleep(1)
pyautogui.press("tab")

# Step 6: Enter Body
body = """Hi,

This is an automated email sent using PyAutoGUI.

Regards,
Python Automation
"""
pyperclip.copy(body)
pyautogui.hotkey("ctrl", "v")
time.sleep(2)

# Step 7: Send Email
pyautogui.hotkey("ctrl", "enter")

print("Email Sent Successfully!")
